physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Initial physical examination, inclusive of a bi-manual pelvic examination, was unremarkable.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Four weeks later, an immobile mass was palpated in the left adnexal region.

physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Exploratory laparotomy revealed 75 mL of ascites; an 8.5-cm left ovarian mass; a 3.5-cm right ovary; and prominent, bilateral pelvic lymphadenopathy.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: After surgery, there was no gross residual disease.
